			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Posted by Orkk Pawn on the Stone Guild message board
<br />
-------------------------------
<br />

<br />
**Everyone READ**
<br />

<br />
AGRO: Friend or Foe 
<br />

<br />
AGRO = Agression = Taunt = What the hell are you talking about? 
<br />

<br />
Ok guys I am writing this because I see issues in AGRO that people do not understand. This blurb is going to cover every aspect of AGRO so when you are finished you will be a ToV, asskick’in, NON-AGRO machine. 
<br />

<br />
AGRO = When a mob is pissed off at you and swinging at your person. Congrats you have obtained AGRO or the mobs aggression is focused on you. 
<br />

<br />
What is AGRO and how is it calculated? 
<br />

<br />
First of all I would like to state that I do not work for Sony, nor have I seen the coding behind AGRO so I am only making assumptions. The key is that my assumptions are the same ones that Tanks everywhere agree upon so they must be right! Well maybe not but if you are in you will be following these same assumptions to make raids move smoothly.\ 
<br />

<br />
First of all I would like you all to think abstractly for a moment. You are a monster (MOB) within Everquest. You are minding your own business and just standing around in the same place all day long. You know only two things within your tiny brain. The only that resides in your puny skull is a LIST which is currently blank and another list of things that are in opposition to your beliefs. We will refer to this blank LIST as the AGRO LIST from this point forward. The OPPOSITION LIST will not be referred to anymore from this point forward. Just be aware that this list might contain things such as, “I am a dark elf guard in neriak and I hate all good races and I will be pissed”, and “I am a dark elf guard in neriak and I hate all evil races that do not follow innoruk and I will be pissed.”, or “I am a dark elf guard that is affiliated with the Dark Elves of America and anyone that is opposing that faction is my enemy and I will be pissed” or “I am a dark elf guard in neriak and if someone attacks me I will be pissed.” 
<br />

<br />
All of the sudden a warrior comes out of no where and gets close to you….well since somewhere on your OPPOSITION LIST, this incoming warrior conflicts with one or more of your beliefs in the OPPOSITION LIST, you move the warriors name into the AGRO LIST. For the purpose of this scenario we will use a random name…… lets say “Orkk”. Orkk has moved into range of a MOB that does not like him for one reason or another and has achieved AGRO. List spot number 1 now contains the Name ORKK. 
<br />

<br />
Different Types of AGRO 
<br />

<br />
1. Range Agro: Weakest form of agro, caused when someone is disliked by the mob and the mob attacks that person. This also comes into play when a tank is hitting a mob and everyone else stands at MAX MELEE range. This is because a mob tends to enjoy hitting a person close to him rather than move to someone standing way far away. So turn on autoattack and then keep moving backwards until it says your target is Out or Range. When it says this, move forward one step to be in range and you are now in MAX Melee range. 
<br />

<br />
2. Sit Agro: Low form of agro caused when a mob dislikes the person but passes by other people it hates and goes for the sitting person because hell….if you had 2 people that you didn’t like and 1 was sitting and 1 was standing…..wouldn’t you go kick the hell out of the sitting person first? 
<br />

<br />
3. Taunt AGRO: This is the ability given to warriors. Yes we actually have a button titled TAUNT. When we hit this it moves us up the imaginary AGRO LIST we have been speaking about. 
<br />

<br />
4. Damage/Delay Agro: No one knows for sure and I am sure everyone will argue with me all day long but both DMG and DLY effect agro on a mob. If I am wielding a weapon that is putting out 10 damage per minute and a friend of mine is putting out 1kdmg per minute with his weapons….he will out taunt me and thus…gain AGRO. This is often why rangers, monks, and rogues pull AGRO off of the main tanks in the group. Tanks are made for taking DMG but do not put out near enough DMG to compete with rogues, monks, rangers. 
<br />

<br />
5. Spell AGRO: ****** THIS IS IMPORTANT***** Spell AGRO is the highest form of AGRO and is what makes or breaks a raid. Anytime you cast a spell on a mob you piss them off severely. Anything that debuffs the mob, slows the mob, Mezzing or charming a mob, or does large amounts of damage to the mob, will cause you to gain large amounts of AGRO and be moved way up his list. THIS IS THE REASON we allow a MT to BUILD agro. This will be further explained in a moment. 
<br />

<br />
6. The Helper AGRO: This agro is somewhere in the list of AGRO but it just depends on how much you are helping. This includes buffing, healing, etc. By doing any of these things on a person, you will be moved up the MOBs AGRO LIST. How much you are moved up depends on the amount of HELP you provided to a person that is on the MOBs AGRO list. This is why Complete Heals causes so much agro. Say you are a ranger and you are getting smoked by some MOB. The cleric casts complete heal on the ranger and just as the ranger is about to die….all his hitpoints are returned. IF YOU WERE A MONSTER….would this not piss you off? This is why clerics have Invulnerability spells. If someone is way up on the AGRO LIST and gets a large heal from someone….the mob moves that healer all the way up to the agro list and goes to town on him/her. 
<br />

<br />
Looking at AGRO on a point system: 
<br />

<br />
Whenever I think of AGRO I like to think of it like a distribution of points. This is the best way I describe this understanding. These points and numbers I am using are ENTIRELY made up but help you understand what is going on behind the scenes. Put yourself back inside the monster again. You have an empty AGRO LIST. This is how you will be affected by a party attacking you. 
<br />

<br />
The party members are as follows: 
<br />

<br />
ORKK (Warrior) 
<br />
GIDO (Warrior) 
<br />
TYMOTHY (Cleric) 
<br />
YOBBA (Monk) 
<br />
HYBREN (Ranger) 
<br />
TEAKKEN (Druid) 
<br />

<br />
The events are the following: 
<br />

<br />
1. GIDO engages the mob and begins to attack (he is moved to the top of the AGRO list) + 1 AGRO 
<br />

<br />
2. Gido hits taunt several times and builds agro (Gido is at the top of the list with a +5 AGRO points next to his name) this is because he has 1 point for being KOS to the mob and 4 points because he has hit taunt 4 times 
<br />

<br />
3. Orkk engages and begins to attack (Orkk does NOT hit Taunt and remains at only +1 agro points because he is also KOS) 
<br />

<br />
4. Yobba and hybren Engage and also obtain 1 Agro point because they are KOS and attacking the mob 
<br />

<br />
5. at this point Gido has +7Agro points because he has hit taunt like 6 times and he is attacking the mob. But UH OH!!! Hybren and Yobba are quickly coming up on his tail because they are putting out way more DMG in a quicker time period (delay) than GIDO. DAMN those Epic HASTES!!!! Hybren and Yobba are now at +5 AGRO each 
<br />

<br />
6. Teakken gets excited and casts a NUKE on the mob. Since the mob is only at 80 percent health and Gido has only obtained +7 agro points, Teakken is about to die. When teakkens uber nuke lands on the mob he obtains +10 agro points because he put out 800dmg in a single blast. The mob has just ran to teakken and quickly destroyed him. 
<br />

<br />
7. Right as Teakken was about to die, Tymothy was chain casting heals on teakken trying to correct is SEVERE mistake he made. Each one of these heals adds +5 AGRO on tymothys name. BTW….tymothys name was not even on the agro list until he landed a heal. After teakken hits the dirt, guess what….Tymothy now has +20agro points and GIDO only has +13..GAH!!!!!! Tymothy dies. 
<br />

<br />
8. Guess who is next on the list, Hybren and yobba are still putting out WAY more dmg and delay than GIDO so they have obtained +14agro points. Hybren dies and Yobba Feign Deaths. 
<br />

<br />
9. Gido is at the top of list because Yobba has feign death which removes his name from the monsters list and orkk and gido are the only ones left. Orkk has not gotten agro because he has not hit taunt and his dmg/dly is similar to Gidos. 
<br />

<br />
10. Eventually GIDO dies because his group is gone. 
<br />

<br />
11. Gido makes a plea for help at the last moment just as he sees Orkk zoning out. 
<br />

<br />

<br />
OK first off…..the people listed in this example DO NOT have this problem at all. I listed these names because I know these are not people that have an issue with this and I am sure they wouldn’t mind being my pawns in this little example J 
<br />

<br />
What was the point of all this? 
<br />

<br />
To show how people move up and down the AGRO list on a MOB. Everything you do moves your name up and down this list. Say for example you are a druid and you cast SNARE while a mob is at like 80 percent health.. The Tank did not have much time to gain AGRO points and your snare just gave yourself +10 agro points….that mob is going to bounce over to you and Tear you a new asshole.
<br />

<br />
THE MORAL OF THIS STORY 
<br />

<br />
Why do we Main Tank? 
<br />

<br />
We let one person build their agro….meaning they put their name at the top of the list and then get as many points as possible next to their name. When that TANK calls ATTACK! They are making the assumption that they have acquired enough points to keep AGRO on themselves the entire fight. 
<br />

<br />
When a Tank calls ATTACK that does not mean everyone! That means MELEE ATTACK! ALL Spell casters will NEVER cast a single spell on a mob until 1 of 2 things takes place.. 1. You have been instructed by the raid to do so. Or 2. The mob is at 60 percent health remaining. The only time you will be instructed otherwise will be if your job is to SLOW or debuff a mob. Often we want a MOB to be SLOWED very soon because a Tank will not like to be shitkicked all over the place with a super fast mob. THIS IS A SEVERE TAUNT! If you are a slower….be ready to take some hits but DO NOT RUN….You do not want to PING PONG the mob all over the place. 
<br />

<br />
If you are NOT a slower….Guess what….YOU WILL NOT ATTACK when the ATTACK is called. If you do…..you will quickly out AGRO the Main TANK and cause a wipeout like the example shown above. 
<br />

<br />
PROPER AGRO Management 
<br />

<br />
Same group as before….lets see what should have happened. 
<br />

<br />

<br />
1. GIDO engages the mob and begins to attack (he is moved to the top of the AGRO list) + 1 AGRO 
<br />

<br />
2. Gido hits taunt several times and builds agro (Gido is at the top of the list with a +5 AGRO points next to his name) this is because he has 1 point for being KOS to the mob and 4 points because he has hit taunt 4 times 
<br />

<br />
3. Orkk engages and begins to attack (Orkk does NOT hit Taunt and remains at only +1 agro points because he is also KOS) orkk is second on the list but only has this 1 point 
<br />

<br />
4. Yobba and hybren Engage and also obtain 1 Agro point because they are KOS and attacking the mob. They are placed as 3rd and 4th on the list but only have 1 point each 
<br />

<br />
5. at this point Gido has +7Agro points because he has hit taunt like 6 times and he is attacking the mob. But UH OH!!! Hybren and Yobba are quickly coming up on his tail because they are putting out way more DMG in a quicker time period (delay) than GIDO. DAMN those Epic HASTES!!!! Hybren and Yobba are now at +5 AGRO each 
<br />

<br />
6. Teakken gets excited and thinks about nuking but checks the mobs health….its only at 90 percent health…hmm TEAKKEN waits 
<br />

<br />
7. Hybren has quickly caught up to GIDO since he is putting out fast and high DMG with his ubbah lightning rods. The mob flips off of Gido and starts hitting Hybren. Hybren turns Off his autoattack and stands still….Gido hits taunt again and gets another +1agro point. This pushes GIDO back up to the top of the list. Does hybren turn back on attack? NOT YET. If he turns it back on right after it flips back to gido he will get the agro again. He waits a few moments and then turns it back on to pursue dmg. 
<br />

<br />
8. Yobba FDs every now and then to try and clear his name from the AGRO LIST. This works sometimes for monks and doesn’t other times. 
<br />

<br />
9. The mob is now at 60 percent health and GIDO has +35 AGRO points. Teakken feels it is time to unleash his wraith!!! He nukes and gets +10 agro points. WOOT he did not out AGRO GIDO and the mob has stayed on GIDO. 
<br />

<br />
10. He nukes a few more times and gets up to +30 agro points….he is closing up on gido but he decides to stop because CHAIN NUKING is a way to out AGRO the Tank very easily. 
<br />

<br />
11. The mob has died. 
<br />

<br />
**NOTE: If you are going to Chain NUKE….you must get under the MOBs belly. You will only chain nuke when told to do so. The reason you will be under the mobs belly is because if you do CHAIN NUKE and OUT AGRO the tank on the 3rd or 4th blast, then the mob will merely kill you where you stand and then move back to the tank. This is VERY IMPORTANT because if you are across the room it will PING PONG the mob all over the place and will cause serious issues. GET UNDER HIM if you are TOLD to CHAIN NUKE! 
<br />

<br />
Conclusion 
<br />

<br />
If none of this makes sense to you then we need to have a serious discussion before the next raid. It is very important that everyone understands what is going on here because we can not accomplish anything without a strong understanding of this concept by every member. If one person does not understand, it will cause an entire raid to fail. 
<br />

<br />
When we are in TOV, Gido will have AGRO the entire time. NO ONE will be hit at all. If you are hit then you did something wrong that was listed in this little guide. 
<br />

<br />
Remember that EVERYTHING you do will effect your name on the AGRO list. When we pull a mob into camp, he has a weak form of agro on the puller because the puller has only pulled the mob. If you are sitting you will be moved to the top and get smoked. If you nuke too soon you will be moved to the top of the agro list. If you cast any spells at all on the mob too soon you will be moved up the list…this includes snare. If you engage too soon you will be moved up to the top of the list. If you stand too close to the mob you will be moved to the top of the list. AND MOST importantly….if you DO NOT PAY ATTENTION you will be moved to the top of the AGRO LIST cause it is almost guaranteed you will do something wrong. 
<br />

<br />
If you are an ubber character that has tons of DMG/DLY and Haste….that’s great but you can also cause a raid to fail. Your uber haste and weapon procs/dmg/dly can cause you to be moved up the AGRO List quicker than anyone else. Take this into account and if you are getting agro…keep turning off your AUTOATTACK and wait some time before turning it back on. If the Tank is not taking DMG then you are putting the RAID at risk.<br />_________________<br />Iksar Shaman 65th Scale
<br />
Lodestar
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=73747">Dead Sexy Lizard</a> Profile
<br />

<br />
