			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">It took me a LOoooong time and a LOT of deaths to figure out agro management on Ely.  Basically, the rules of thumb are:
<br />

<br />
If you don't have high dps going on on the mob, don't hit with a stack of high dpt dots.  You will, about haflway the fight, out damage the folks beating on the mob.  DoT agro is evil and usually can't be shaken.
<br />

<br />
Snare and druid debuffs are the ULTIMATE taunt.  Land a snare and then a debuff right behind it, you are at the top of the list.  For that reason, I either a) get inside range to cast so that the mob doesn't ping pong or b) land the debuff at about 90% and the snare at about 40%.  Other stuff gets the mobs attention in between.  If you can't land the snare right off, don't hit the button again immediately, or if you do, warn someone that you are probably going to get agro...you will.
<br />

<br />
Sitting down during a fight, if you've cast almost anything at the beginning, is bad.
<br />

<br />
Complete Heals as the puller is incoming are also bad.
<br />

<br />
ALWAYS have root up....it's the only invulnerability that you have.  
<br />

<br />
All of that being said, there are times when agro is a very useful tool for a druid.  In ToV, I've used it to pull mobs through the doors.  I've used it to pull large stacks of mobs off of a group in order to kite them.  (Couple of snares and the mob is yours.)  In some cases, I've pulled it off of the MT because of the hp's...(although that usually ends up with ME getting munched while the tank is healing....c'est la guerre).  The trick is knowing when to get it, when to not get it and where to BE if you intend to get it.  It is also about communicating with your group, especially if there is another healer, and letting THEM know what you are up to.<br />_________________<br /><img src="http://www.eq-lodestar.com/images/dark_powers.jpg"><br>Elyssia Stormbow
<br />
Druid - 65th Season
<br />

<br />
In a sky full of people, only some learn to fly.  Isn't that crazy?  
<br />
~Seal~</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
