			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I have to say that I think a lot of his information is wrong.
<br />

<br />
First off...MT on a critter until 80% health???  For almost any critter that means that everyone else but the healer and the slower can go make a sandwich (take your time!).
<br />

<br />
His guide was obviously mainly written for total raid newbies but hopefully everyone did get something out of it.
<br />

<br />
The MT will call assist by 95% at the latest.  Most other melee have aggro reducer tricks and the ones that don't really aren't likely to get aggro anyway (unless they purposely try).
<br />

<br />
Nukers wait until 60% health?  Yeah, right...we want the thing dead today, please. :p
<br />

<br />
HERE'S THE BIG SECRET:
<br />

<br />
If you even SUSPECT the spell you're about to cast will get aggro, BE UP CLOSE & PERSONAL WITH THE CRITTER.  You may get hit, but being THAT close to the critter means that the tank will almost positively be able to get aggro back before you die.
<br />

<br />
I think most of our guild knows about sit aggro but restating it:  STAND WHEN INC.  STAND FOR A FEW SECONDS AFTER NUKING OR DOTTING.  STAND FOR A FEW SECONDS AFTER SENDING A PET.  *Please* the first time you sit, be within melee range of the critter...we don't need to find out about sit aggro after he runs away from us and to you.  PING PONG IS EVIL.
<br />

<br />
But, if you're up close & personal feel free to nuke and dot when assist is called.  You should know your class well enough to know when enough is enough (to avoid aggro).  Again, if you do goof, BE IN MELEE RANGE.
<br />

<br />
And like Ely said, please don't over do DOTs. :p<br />_________________<br />Binnen Minder
<br />
Gnome God At-Large (so to speak)
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=977280" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=977280</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
