::ahem:: might want to reword that to "the only one that I haven't been able to steal it from, who was always TRYING to keep aggro...has been Baldy <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="icon_wink.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
I sometimes let a mob (if its not dire or a total wipe situation) lax on me a bit...but I do it for a reason. I check the counters on the mob and sometimes if I see a situation where a shamen is having difficulty slowing, I keep aggro on the border. In Multipe Mob Situation...the Gloves are off... 
<br />

<br />
Hint: With the proper pally spell line off..I have kept aggro on me even from most. The ONLY one's that I had to work and work hard at keeping it, was one particular Pally in Group (DH), and a Particular Manaburning Wizards (One YH and surprisingly One DBoN Wizard). That is..if they are trying to steal aggro and I am 100% Focused on that mob. There are events....where its chaos and well..not much anyone can do about that <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="icon_wink.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
