			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">It does irk me a tad if every mob is being rooted the second it reaches camp (because that's not probably necessary).  But rooting a mez'd mob, for example, so that the MT can break mez without worrying about taking time to taunt first, is a nice touch.  I've also seen casters root mobs because they couldn't get off some other important spell that was being interrupted... root can buy them time to back up and land a slow or tash or what-have-you.  
<br />

<br />
In group (non-raid) situations, I don't have a problem with it.... so long as they announce to the group that they are doing it.  That way, I know to get right in the mob's face for proximity aggro, and other melee know to step back if they are getting hit.
<br />

<br />
Riliana Steelthong<br />_________________<br />Riliana Steelthong
