			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">If I have a warrior tank I do one of 2 things...  I either us bow damage exclusively if the remainder of teh group is fairly low aggro classes OR higher aggro melee classes that can take a bit of roughing up if the mob turns.  OR, I get in and melee building just enough aggro to be on the hate list fairly close to the top if some of the other classes tend to cause aggro frequently.  The reason for this is simple.  Say Xabiktik is there trying to get the mob slowed and has 3 resists so far.  Warrior is going to have a heck of a time out aggroing 3 back to back slow resists.  A quick snare and a taunt and I can grab the aggro from the chanter.  Granted the warrior doesn't have aggro at this point but being a good warrior they are now actively mashing taunt and disarm for all it is worth building up aggro as fast as they can.  Meanwhile Xab got his slow off and can leave the mob alone.  warrior has built good aggro by now but I still have it.  I ALWAYS have Jolt memmed.  Attack off, Jolt once, Warrior has aggro and I back off to do bow damage.  If I have a GOOD Pally or SK then I just do bow DPS since I do better damage that way.
<br />

<br />
Another reason Riliana would like me in the group besides aggro control?  That lousy good for nothing root.  Nobody dislikes a rooted mob more than a ranger.  In case you did not know this, if the mob is free to roam about (snared is fine) but chooses to stand still to either beat on a tank or cast a spell, every bow shot that lands on this mob registers as "your bow shot has done double damage" That's right DOUBLE the DPS.  If you root that same mob you have cut the DPS of rangers in half.  If I cut all your nuke damage in half you wouldn't like me much would you?  SO, if I see my bow not doing double damage on a mob standing there beating down on a tank I will be nuking your roots free until I get the message that I am doing double damage again =)<br />_________________<br /><B> <I> <A HREF = "http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=225793">Ialyeni Ianda </A></I> </B>  
<br />
lvl 65 Forest stalker
<br />

<br />
Deadly with the bow and fleet of foot.
<br />
When trouble arrives there is no need to call, no need to even turn around, for he is there for you, rest assured.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
